      "id": "PopularPost331995",
      "post_content": "@Notus  \nNo, because you have to pay {1} for every target beyond the first. Casting it for {r} would work on one illusion, but not all of them. You'd have to effectively pay {r} for each target.  \nThe logic of \"even 0 damage is enough to destroy them\" still stands though, which is why it's hilarious playing [Bonfire of the Damned](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bonfire of the Damned) for {r}{r} (or even {r} if you miracle it out) and watching the boardwipe.",
      "posted_by": "Ginto",
